## Resolution (2026-07-12)

Done, split across two flagg sessions (correction: the "concurrent flagg-side session" and "this session" were both ON flagg — this session spent 20 minutes believing it was on blaine because it never ran `hostname -s`; that failure is now a machine-identity rule in flagg's `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md` and a memory note).

- **Infra** (sibling session, wiki repo `bab24f1`): Vercel DNS `brain.joelclaw.com` A → 100.113.161.65; Caddyfile serves `brain.joelclaw.com` (LE DNS-01 via Vercel) and 308-redirects `daily.joelclaw.com`; Caddy restarted (note in Caddyfile: restart, don't exec-reload — the ro bind mount pins the old inode).
- **Verified** (this session): pinned to the sidecar IP, `https://brain.joelclaw.com/` returns **200**; `daily` returns **308 → brain`; a lingering 404 from flagg's own resolver was stale wildcard DNS (Vercel `DEPLOYMENT_NOT_FOUND`), already resolving correctly on cell networks — propagation, not breakage.
- **Fleet cleanup** (this session): dark-wizard `wiki-aware.block.md` now names brain.joelclaw.com and the Brain Graph arc, grafts refreshed, pushed (`3be2d72`) — blaine/panda pick it up on next dw-sync. `daily-joelclaw-wiki-topology` memory note updated. `joelclaw-wiki/AGENTS.md` had no daily.joelclaw.com references to fix.
- Acceptance item 1 of the map is done: brain.joelclaw.com serves the wiki, daily redirects.
